## DP-700 ‚Äì Implement & Manage an Analytics Solution  
### Orchestrate Processes: Choose between Dataflow Gen2, Pipeline, and Notebook

---

## üìå Tool Comparison (High-Yield)

| Requirement      | Dataflow Gen2           | Fabric Pipeline        | Fabric Notebook       |
|------------------|-------------------------|------------------------|-----------------------|
| Purpose          | Ingest & transform data | Orchestration          | Complex processing    |
| Code required    | ‚ùå No                   | ‚ùå No                  | ‚úÖ Yes                |
| Transform type   | Power Query             | None                   | PySpark / SQL         |
| Scheduling       | ‚úÖ Yes                  | ‚úÖ Yes                 | ‚ö†Ô∏è Via Pipeline       |
| Failure handling | ‚ùå Limited              | ‚úÖ Yes                 | ‚ö†Ô∏è Via Pipeline       |
| Big data / Spark | ‚ùå No                   | ‚ùå No                  | ‚úÖ Yes                |
| Analyst-friendly | ‚úÖ Yes                  | ‚ö†Ô∏è Neutral             | ‚ùå No                 |

---

## üîπ Dataflow Gen2

**Key Concepts**
- Low-code / no-code ingestion  
- Power Query transformations  
- Analyst-driven  

**Use When**
- SaaS or relational sources  
- Basic‚Äìmoderate transformations  
- Scheduled refresh  
- No Spark or Python required  

**Configuration / Settings**
- Power Query editor  
- On-prem gateway (if needed)  
- Destination: Lakehouse or Warehouse  

**Scope**
- Workspace-level  

**Avoid When**
- Very large datasets  
- Complex joins or custom logic  

---

## üîπ Fabric Pipeline

**Key Concepts**
- Orchestration & control flow  
- Sequencing, retries, dependencies  
- Central monitoring  

**Use When**
- Run items in a specific order  
- Trigger Dataflows, Notebooks, SQL scripts  
- Failure handling is required  

**Configuration / Settings**
- Activities (Notebook, Dataflow, Copy Data)  
- Dependency conditions  
- Retry policies  

**Scope**
- Workspace-level  

**Avoid When**
- Only transformations are needed  

---

## üîπ Fabric Notebook

**Key Concepts**
- Code-first analytics  
- Spark-based execution  
- High performance & scalability  

**Use When**
- Big data processing  
- Complex transformations  
- PySpark / Python / SQL logic  
- Performance tuning required  

**Configuration / Settings**
- Spark configuration  
- Libraries  
- Parameters  

**Scope**
- Workspace-level  

**Avoid When**
- No-code requirement  
- Simple ingestion scenarios  

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Exam Traps & Tips

**Common Traps**
- ‚ùå Using Notebook for simple ingestion  
- ‚ùå Using Spark when Power Query is sufficient  
- ‚ùå Forgetting Pipeline for orchestration  

**Decision Shortcuts (Memorize)**
- No-code + SaaS ‚Üí **Dataflow Gen2**  
- Run X then Y then Z ‚Üí **Fabric Pipeline**  
- PySpark + big data ‚Üí **Notebook**  
- End-to-end flow ‚Üí **Pipeline + (Dataflow / Notebook)**  

---

